

Kubernetes
•	Kubernetes is an open-source Container Management Tool which automates Container Deployment, Container Scaling & Container Load Balancing.
•	It schedules, run and manages isolated containers such are running on Virtual machine/Cloud Machines.
•	All top Cloud providers support Kubernetes.

Cloud Based K8s Services: -
GKE= Google Kubernetes Service.
AKS= Azure Kubernetes Service.
Amazon EKS= Elastic Kubernetes Service.

Kubernetes Installation Tools: -
-	Minikube
-	Kubeadm
Problems with scaling up the containers: - 
•	Containers cannot communicate with each other.
•	Autoscaling and load Balancing was not possible.
•	Containers had to be moved carefully.

